      <td width="178">
        <p><img src="/img/boat.gif" width="300" height="150"></p>
        <p><img src="/img/bouy.jpg" width="300" height="198"></p>
        <p><img src="/img/pfd.jpg" width="300" height="248"></p>
      </td>
      <td width="306"> 
        <p align="center"><img src="/img/jacket.gif" width="75" height="108"></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><b><font size="2">How 
          can you be safe while you're boating?</font></b></font></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"> Wear a 
          P.F.D. (Personal Flotation Device, sometimes called a life jacket) even 
          if you have been on a boat before and can swim.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"> Plan ahead 
          and check the weather forecast for the weather when you go boating or 
          go on a boating trip for the weekend or just a ride. </font></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">You have 
          to be 16 years or older to drive a boat. To drive a boat you also have 
          to take a mail-in test that you mail in when you're done taking the 
          test. Then you're approved to drive a boat. </font></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">It's against 
          the law if you pass a buoy if you don't read or obey the buoy. It is 
          against the law to drive a boat in a swimming area with a sign that 
          says "KEEP OUT... SWIMMING AREA".</font></p>
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">It's against 
          the law to drive a boat loaded with too many people. You can not drive 
          irresponsibly. You need to sit in the boat area and not lean over the 
          edge.</font> </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
